\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.1}{\ignorespaces Five phases of the cardiac action potential. Phase 0: rapid depolarization (inward $\text {Na}^+$ current). Phase 1: early repolarization (outward $\text {K}^+$ current). Phase 2: plateau (inward $\text {Ca}^{2+}$ current balances outward $\text {K}^+$). Phase 3: rapid repolarization. Phase 4: resting state.}}{4}{figure.caption.6}%
